1
00:00:01,793 --> 00:00:04,171
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:24,459
[rattling]

3
00:01:31,508 --> 00:01:33,343
[door thuds]

4
00:01:37,889 --> 00:01:41,018
[Light] How many seconds has it been
since you wrote down the first name?

5
00:01:43,562 --> 00:01:47,649
Thirty-five, 36, 37,

6
00:01:47,983 --> 00:01:50,694
thirty-eight, 39...

7
00:01:51,445 --> 00:01:53,655
Well, Near, looks like I win.

8
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:55,240
[Mikami] Forty!

9
00:01:55,407 --> 00:01:58,702
NEW WORLD

10
00:02:10,255 --> 00:02:11,632
[both shuddering]

11
00:02:14,593 --> 00:02:15,636
[Matsuda] Huh?

12
00:02:19,014 --> 00:02:20,390
We're still alive.

13
00:02:21,808 --> 00:02:24,686
It's been over a minute
and we haven't died!

14
00:02:26,938 --> 00:02:30,317
Didn't I already tell you all
that no one was gonna die?

15
00:02:30,692 --> 00:02:33,278
[Mikami stammering] But why?

16
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:35,864
Why won't they die?

17
00:02:35,989 --> 00:02:36,907
[shuddering breathing]

18
00:02:37,032 --> 00:02:37,908
[Mikami] God!

19
00:02:38,492 --> 00:02:40,744
I did everything you told me!

20
00:02:40,827 --> 00:02:42,788
Rester, Gevanni, take him now!

21
00:02:42,954 --> 00:02:47,292
[Mikami yelling frantically]

22
00:02:49,628 --> 00:02:51,546
Gevanni, the notebook, please.

23
00:02:55,050 --> 00:02:57,678
If you didn't believe me earlier,
then see for yourselves.

24
00:02:57,928 --> 00:03:00,514
KANZO MOGI TOUTA MATSUDA
HIDEKI IDE SHUICHI AIZAWA

25
00:03:00,639 --> 00:03:04,059
I can confirm that the first four names
are definitely the real names

26
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:05,477
of the SPK members.

27
00:03:05,727 --> 00:03:07,854
The second four are the names
of your team.

28
00:03:07,979 --> 00:03:09,940
The only name that hasn't
been written down...

29
00:03:10,065 --> 00:03:11,358
is Light Yagami.

30
00:03:11,733 --> 00:03:12,943
[snarling]

31
00:03:13,318 --> 00:03:16,655
[Near] If that weren't enough,
Mikami also addressed you as "God,"

32
00:03:16,822 --> 00:03:18,657
and said he did what you asked him to.

33
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:20,909
It's settled.

34
00:03:23,286 --> 00:03:24,413
[Light breathes shakily]

35
00:03:24,579 --> 00:03:27,457
It's a trap! This whole thing is a setup!

36
00:03:27,791 --> 00:03:30,168
This is all part of Near's plan
to frame me!

37
00:03:30,544 --> 00:03:32,212
Isn't it a little odd that no one died

38
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:34,214
after having their name
written in the notebook?

39
00:03:34,297 --> 00:03:36,133
This proves it's a trap!

40
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:37,801
[Matsuda gasps]

41
00:03:38,176 --> 00:03:40,637
[whimpering]

42
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:43,473
I believe I already told you
that no one would die

43
00:03:43,598 --> 00:03:45,934
-because I modified the notebook.
-[Light gasps]

44
00:03:46,309 --> 00:03:48,353
No! You-- [panting]

45
00:03:49,146 --> 00:03:50,856
[huffs] That can't be!

46
00:03:53,275 --> 00:03:55,569
This is a setup. I don't know this guy!

47
00:03:55,944 --> 00:03:59,614
[begins sobbing]

48
00:04:01,408 --> 00:04:04,411
Light, it's too late to deny it.
You know Near has won.

49
00:04:04,911 --> 00:04:07,914
Just a moment ago, you were saying,
"It looks like I win."

50
00:04:08,457 --> 00:04:10,667
How much more of a confession
do we need?

51
00:04:15,714 --> 00:04:16,715
[Matsuda] Light...

52
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:21,303
Why?

53
00:04:28,143 --> 00:04:29,895
[gasps] Stop it!

54
00:04:30,353 --> 00:04:34,399
[yelling in panic]

55
00:04:34,566 --> 00:04:38,028
[panting]

56
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:44,701
Light Yagami. L. Kira.

57
00:04:45,994 --> 00:04:48,121
It's over. You've lost the game.

58
00:04:51,541 --> 00:04:54,085
Just a moment ago,
you proclaimed your victory,

59
00:04:54,211 --> 00:04:55,879
expecting us all to die.

60
00:04:56,129 --> 00:04:59,216
And to tell the truth,
you might've actually won.

61
00:04:59,549 --> 00:05:01,134
And I would've lost.

62
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:05,055
We ended up doing exactly
what you expected us to,

63
00:05:05,138 --> 00:05:08,058
and altered the fake notebook
in Mikami's possession.

64
00:05:10,352 --> 00:05:13,313
However, when I said before
that we had modified the notebook,

65
00:05:13,396 --> 00:05:16,691
I was in fact referring
to the real notebook as well as the fake.

66
00:05:17,192 --> 00:05:18,068
[gasps]

67
00:05:18,693 --> 00:05:20,987
We only switched part
of the fake notebook.

68
00:05:21,154 --> 00:05:24,699
But as for the real one,
we replaced the entire thing.

69
00:05:25,158 --> 00:05:27,410
This notebook here
is actually the real one.

70
00:05:27,536 --> 00:05:30,789
[gasps] No! Impossible!

71
00:05:30,872 --> 00:05:33,208
[Near] We used the same kind
of pen that Mikami used,

72
00:05:33,375 --> 00:05:34,876
copied his handwriting perfectly,

73
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:37,254
and made both the inside
and the outside of our fake

74
00:05:37,337 --> 00:05:38,797
look exactly like the original.

75
00:05:39,464 --> 00:05:42,425
Gevanni was able to do it
in a single night.

76
00:05:45,929 --> 00:05:49,266
Of course, since I had touched
the real notebook before coming,

77
00:05:49,349 --> 00:05:51,685
I've been able to see the Shinigami
as well.

78
00:05:51,977 --> 00:05:53,311
-Ah...
-[Aizawa] Huh?

79
00:05:53,812 --> 00:05:57,399
It's a pleasure to meet you,
Mr. Shinigami. I'm Near.

80
00:05:57,732 --> 00:06:02,195
[cackles] Nice to meet you too.
My name is Ryuk.

81
00:06:02,362 --> 00:06:03,864
[Light] He can talk to Ryuk.

82
00:06:04,614 --> 00:06:07,450
He can see him, so that means...
it must be true.

83
00:06:08,368 --> 00:06:10,912
[Near] Some of the edges
of this notebook's pages are torn.

84
00:06:11,079 --> 00:06:14,124
Tell me, if someone's name was written
on a ripped off piece of paper,

85
00:06:14,249 --> 00:06:15,250
would they still die?

86
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,335
Oh, yeah. Of course they would.

87
00:06:17,502 --> 00:06:18,545
[Near] I thought so.

88
00:06:18,795 --> 00:06:21,131
I bet you were able to use that
to your advantage.

89
00:06:22,424 --> 00:06:27,220
I wonder how many times you deceived us
with this, and how many people you killed.

90
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:32,309
Light Yagami, you are Kira.

91
00:06:37,272 --> 00:06:39,024
[Light] This has gotta be a trick.

92
00:06:39,441 --> 00:06:41,735
Or could it be that Mikami's betrayed me
somehow?

93
00:06:41,818 --> 00:06:43,403
-[Near] You're mistaken.
-[gasps]

94
00:06:43,612 --> 00:06:45,363
This was all thanks to Mello.

95
00:06:46,323 --> 00:06:49,451
I believe if I explain this much,
you'll begin to understand.

96
00:06:49,743 --> 00:06:51,578
[Light] What? Mello?

97
00:06:51,661 --> 00:06:53,997
Please take a look at this page
of the notebook.

98
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:55,749
[gasps]

99
00:06:55,874 --> 00:06:57,083
KIYOMI TAKADA SUICIDE
BURNS TO DEATH

100
00:06:57,167 --> 00:06:58,627
[Light] Takada's name is in the notebook!

101
00:06:58,710 --> 00:07:00,503
[panting] I was the one who killed her,

102
00:07:00,629 --> 00:07:02,505
but her death was written there
just one minute later.

103
00:07:02,589 --> 00:07:03,465
JANUARY 26 2:33 PM

104
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:07,010
Does that mean Mikami
did the same thing I did?

105
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:10,722
God! You told me you couldn't move freely.

106
00:07:11,222 --> 00:07:13,767
I had to make sure Takada
was taken care of!

107
00:07:13,934 --> 00:07:15,518
Wasn't that my duty to you?

108
00:07:15,685 --> 00:07:16,561
[Light] You idiot!

109
00:07:16,645 --> 00:07:20,398
I gave you strict orders not to make
any unnecessary movements until today!

110
00:07:21,066 --> 00:07:22,150
It's all true.

111
00:07:22,317 --> 00:07:23,276
On the 26th,

112
00:07:23,401 --> 00:07:26,196
right after Takada's kidnapping
was broadcast on the news,

113
00:07:26,321 --> 00:07:28,031
Mikami went to the bank.

114
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:30,533
I've been trailing him.

115
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:34,037
I knew he went to the bank
everyone month on the 25th.

116
00:07:34,746 --> 00:07:40,001
So, it was odd for someone so methodical
to go to the bank twice in two days.

117
00:07:40,251 --> 00:07:43,797
I followed Mikami to the bank as he headed
for the safe deposit boxes.

118
00:07:44,047 --> 00:07:46,508
It was only at this time
that he seemed concerned

119
00:07:46,591 --> 00:07:48,677
whether someone was following him or not.

120
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:54,015
I got into his safe deposit box.
Inside was the real notebook.

121
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:58,019
Sure enough, Takada's name had already
been written inside it.

122
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:01,940
[Near] Do you understand now,
Light Yagami?

123
00:08:02,107 --> 00:08:04,567
You didn't realize
that Mikami made a move on his own

124
00:08:04,651 --> 00:08:06,361
and wrote Takada's name in his notebook

125
00:08:06,486 --> 00:08:09,781
because you had already killed her
using a notebook clipping yourself.

126
00:08:10,323 --> 00:08:14,119
This was the event that made me consider
the possibility of a fake notebook.

127
00:08:14,327 --> 00:08:17,205
We were able to stop you
thanks to the efforts of one person.

128
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:19,541
It was Mello who did it all.

129
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:24,546
[Lidner] Mello probably knew
what was going to happen all along.

130
00:08:26,089 --> 00:08:29,009
[Mello] It can be resolved by having
a name written in the notebook?

131
00:08:29,426 --> 00:08:30,385
That's right.

132
00:08:32,762 --> 00:08:35,265
[Mello] Well then, if I don't do it...

133
00:08:37,017 --> 00:08:38,893
I bet Mello knew in his heart

134
00:08:39,227 --> 00:08:42,856
that working by ourselves, neither of us
would be able to attain our goal.

135
00:08:42,981 --> 00:08:44,858
and surpass our mentor, L.

136
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:47,527
But together...

137
00:08:48,236 --> 00:08:50,363
together, we can stand with L.

138
00:08:50,739 --> 00:08:52,407
Together, we can surpass L!

139
00:08:52,782 --> 00:08:56,786
And now, acting as one,
we face the Kira who defeated L,

140
00:08:56,995 --> 00:08:59,497
and with solid evidence,
beat him at his own game!

141
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:06,671
Let's see you try and talk your way
out of this one... if you can.

142
00:09:16,806 --> 00:09:21,394
[Light laughs softly]

143
00:09:21,895 --> 00:09:25,190
[laughing intensifies]

144
00:09:25,315 --> 00:09:30,653
[laughing maniacally]

145
00:09:40,914 --> 00:09:42,290
[Light] That's right...

146
00:09:44,709 --> 00:09:46,336
I am Kira.

147
00:10:06,648 --> 00:10:09,359
That's right. I am Kira.

148
00:10:11,402 --> 00:10:13,488
And what can you do?

149
00:10:14,989 --> 00:10:16,658
Kill me right here?

150
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:22,705
Hear this. I'm not only Kira.

151
00:10:23,331 --> 00:10:25,083
But I'm also...

152
00:10:25,917 --> 00:10:27,669
God of the new world!

153
00:10:29,838 --> 00:10:32,757
Kira has become law in the world
we now live.

154
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:35,385
He's the one who's maintaining order.

155
00:10:36,219 --> 00:10:37,929
I have become Justice.

156
00:10:38,847 --> 00:10:40,598
The only hope for mankind.

157
00:10:41,182 --> 00:10:42,851
[snickers] Kill me?

158
00:10:44,102 --> 00:10:46,271
Is that really the right thing to do?

159
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:52,152
Since Kira's appearance six years ago,
wars have stopped

160
00:10:52,277 --> 00:10:55,196
and global crime rates have been
reduced by over 70 percent.

161
00:10:56,197 --> 00:11:00,034
But, it's not enough.
This world is still rotten!

162
00:11:00,368 --> 00:11:02,370
With too many rotten people.

163
00:11:05,748 --> 00:11:07,625
Somebody has to do this!

164
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:11,296
When I first got that notebook,
all those years ago,

165
00:11:11,462 --> 00:11:13,173
I knew I had to do it.

166
00:11:13,673 --> 00:11:17,051
No, I was the only one who could!

167
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:21,264
I understood that killing people
was a crime...

168
00:11:21,431 --> 00:11:22,599
[glass shattering]

169
00:11:22,724 --> 00:11:26,269
There was no other way!
The world had to be fixed!

170
00:11:26,436 --> 00:11:28,062
A purpose given to me!

171
00:11:30,648 --> 00:11:32,192
Only I could do it.

172
00:11:34,027 --> 00:11:37,739
Who else could have done it?
And come this far?

173
00:11:37,822 --> 00:11:39,282
Would they have kept going?

174
00:11:41,618 --> 00:11:42,911
The only one...

175
00:11:44,329 --> 00:11:49,083
who can create a new world... is me.

176
00:11:55,215 --> 00:11:58,551
No. You're just a murderer, Light Yagami.

177
00:11:58,885 --> 00:12:02,013
And this notebook is the deadliest
weapon of mass murder

178
00:12:02,096 --> 00:12:03,890
in the history of mankind.

179
00:12:05,642 --> 00:12:08,353
You yielded to the power
of the Shinigami and the notebook.

180
00:12:08,811 --> 00:12:11,272
And you have confused yourself
with a god.

181
00:12:11,481 --> 00:12:14,317
In the end, you're nothing more
than a crazy serial killer.

182
00:12:14,734 --> 00:12:16,402
That's all you are.

183
00:12:17,528 --> 00:12:20,031
Nothing more and nothing less.

184
00:12:36,381 --> 00:12:40,468
[Light] Useless fools.
As if they could ever understand.

185
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:56,401
[Light] Near.

186
00:12:57,777 --> 00:13:00,780
Here's some food for thought.
That notebook you have,

187
00:13:00,905 --> 00:13:04,033
and the one that Aizawa brought
from the Japanese Task Force Headquarters.

188
00:13:05,285 --> 00:13:06,577
Are they both real?

189
00:13:07,662 --> 00:13:09,914
[Near] What is he up to?
Is he bluffing?

190
00:13:11,249 --> 00:13:14,544
[Light] At the moment, only I know
where the real notebook is.

191
00:13:16,629 --> 00:13:20,300
If you truly wanna defeat Kira,
as well as test the notebook

192
00:13:20,383 --> 00:13:21,592
that Aizawa's carrying...

193
00:13:23,511 --> 00:13:27,849
I guess you're gonna have to write down
either my name or Mikami's.

194
00:13:32,603 --> 00:13:35,106
It's the only way to see if it's real...

195
00:13:37,025 --> 00:13:38,401
or fake!

196
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:41,154
He's hidden a piece of the notebook!

197
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:43,489
[Light yells]

198
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:45,575
Matsuda!

199
00:13:48,619 --> 00:13:49,746
[growling]

200
00:13:50,496 --> 00:13:52,081
Matsuda, you idiot!

201
00:13:53,041 --> 00:13:55,585
Who the hell do you think
you're shooting at?

202
00:13:56,085 --> 00:13:57,920
Don't screw with me!

203
00:13:59,839 --> 00:14:01,424
What was it all for, then?

204
00:14:02,175 --> 00:14:05,428
What about your dad?
What the hell did he die for?

205
00:14:05,595 --> 00:14:07,180
[wheezing] My dad?

206
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:10,600
[laughs] You mean Soichiro Yagami?

207
00:14:11,184 --> 00:14:12,518
That's right, Matsuda!

208
00:14:12,643 --> 00:14:15,938
In this world, all those earnest people
like him who fight for justice,

209
00:14:16,064 --> 00:14:20,401
they always lose. You want a world where
people like that are made to be fools?

210
00:14:20,651 --> 00:14:23,321
I know you understand, so kill the others!

211
00:14:24,238 --> 00:14:25,656
Shoot them!

212
00:14:27,158 --> 00:14:29,327
You led your own father to his death.

213
00:14:30,161 --> 00:14:32,288
And now he's gone, you call him a fool?

214
00:14:37,835 --> 00:14:39,420
-His blood!
-[Matsuda yells]

215
00:14:39,587 --> 00:14:42,590
[gunshots]

216
00:14:45,927 --> 00:14:47,303
-I'll kill him!
-[Light gasping for air]

217
00:14:47,428 --> 00:14:49,847
I'll kill him! He has to die!

218
00:14:49,972 --> 00:14:51,516
[gunshot echoing]

219
00:15:03,611 --> 00:15:09,117
[Matsuda whimpering]

220
00:15:10,451 --> 00:15:12,078
[Light grunting]

221
00:15:12,412 --> 00:15:13,913
[Light] Damn you.

222
00:15:14,163 --> 00:15:16,707
What the hell is this?

223
00:15:20,878 --> 00:15:23,756
Mikami! What are you waiting for?

224
00:15:25,383 --> 00:15:26,843
Write down their names!

225
00:15:27,260 --> 00:15:31,764
Write them down! Kill them now!

226
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:33,850
[Mikami breathing shakily]

227
00:15:35,143 --> 00:15:38,271
[Mogi] It's finally over, isn't it Near?

228
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:39,856
[Near] Yes.

229
00:15:41,149 --> 00:15:43,276
[wheezing]

230
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:46,404
Where are you Misa?

231
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:49,365
Where's Takada? [sobs]

232
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:56,539
[wheezing] Someone...

233
00:15:59,917 --> 00:16:02,295
[sobbing] What do I do now?

234
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:08,217
[Mikami screaming]

235
00:16:17,143 --> 00:16:18,060
Mikami!

236
00:16:18,311 --> 00:16:20,188
[Mikami screaming]

237
00:16:21,272 --> 00:16:22,773
[Aikawa] Quick. Stop the bleeding!

238
00:16:22,899 --> 00:16:24,192
[Gevanni] It's already too late.

239
00:16:24,525 --> 00:16:26,319
He'll be dead in a few seconds.

240
00:16:41,876 --> 00:16:43,252
Wait, Light!

241
00:16:43,377 --> 00:16:44,545
[gasps]

242
00:16:45,338 --> 00:16:47,006
He's getting away! Light!

243
00:16:47,173 --> 00:16:48,549
-[Near] Mr. Aizawa!
-Huh?

244
00:16:49,592 --> 00:16:52,094
It's unlikely he has any more pieces
of the notebook.

245
00:16:52,553 --> 00:16:55,473
And with those wounds,
he's not going to go far.

246
00:16:55,848 --> 00:16:58,226
He'll stop running soon,
even if we leave him alone.

247
00:16:58,935 --> 00:17:02,730
Huh. Near, I'm not gonna follow
your orders.

248
00:17:02,855 --> 00:17:03,731
Huh?

249
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:07,902
Very well, then. I'll leave it up to you.

250
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:18,079
[Light breathing shakily]

251
00:17:50,570 --> 00:17:52,947
[Light begins sobbing]

252
00:17:58,411 --> 00:18:02,707
[panting]

253
00:18:47,293 --> 00:18:50,296
[Ryuk] Well, Light,
it looks like you've lost.

254
00:18:51,130 --> 00:18:54,216
Remember how, in the beginning,
when we first met,

255
00:18:54,675 --> 00:18:58,429
I told you that I'd be the one
writing your name in my notebook?

256
00:19:01,766 --> 00:19:03,809
That is part of the agreement

257
00:19:03,976 --> 00:19:07,980
between a Shinigami who brings a notebook
to the human world...

258
00:19:08,606 --> 00:19:10,900
and the first human who picks it up.

259
00:19:14,528 --> 00:19:17,782
If they put you in prison,
who knows when you'd die?

260
00:19:18,699 --> 00:19:20,785
And I don't wanna lie around waiting.

261
00:19:21,786 --> 00:19:24,664
So, it's all over.

262
00:19:27,208 --> 00:19:28,834
You'll die here.

263
00:19:36,842 --> 00:19:38,886
It was good while it lasted.

264
00:19:39,095 --> 00:19:41,847
We eased each other's boredom
for quite a while.

265
00:19:46,644 --> 00:19:50,272
Well, Light, it's been interesting.

266
00:19:50,398 --> 00:19:51,440
LIGHT YAGAMI

267
00:20:21,011 --> 00:20:24,348
[soft piano music playing]
